cs.MS, cs.PL, cs.SE, cs.SC, cs.CE 

This paper is about a library aimed at simplifying the conversion of MATLAB/Octave code to Julia, a new programming language for technical computing. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the following sub-categories: 

- cs.MS (Mathematical Software): This sub-category covers software related to mathematical computation, which is the main focus of the paper. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages): This sub-category covers research related to programming languages, which is relevant to the development of Julia and the comparison with MATLAB/Octave. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering): This sub-category covers research related to software development, which is relevant to the modernization of research workflows mentioned in the abstract. 
- cs.SC (Symbolic Computation): This sub-category covers research related to symbolic computation, which is a common use case for MATLAB/Octave and Julia. 
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science): This sub-category covers research related to computational methods in various fields, which is relevant to the image analysis use case presented in the paper.
